This file describes the configuration and settings done to prepare the PYTHON environment used to develop and execute
the REVERSI program.

Change directory to $REVERSI_HOME/c:

  $ cd $REVERSI_HOME/c

Then run to activate the VENV, start PYTHON, and load the REVESI libraries:

  $ source py/.reversi_venv/bin/activate
  $ python3
  >>> exec(open("py/reversi/start.py").read())

In order to compute a simple sample model execute:

  >>> m = rglm_workflow(test_run_0)